    • Method Detail

      • getType

        public FlowObjectGatewayImpl.Type getType()
        Returns the type of an Event. It defines the split behavior of this Gateway. For an exclusive gateways, only one outgoing sequence flow is used (XOR). For an inclusive gateway, all are used which have a condition that is true (OR). For a parallel gateway, all outgoing sequence flows are executed in parallel with no conditions (AND). A Complex gateway defines a custom rule to select outgoing sequence flows.
        Returns:
        type of this gateway
